      <heading>Sat Dec 23 (Taval)      :: Muan's BG</heading>
      <slot>7</slot>
      <level>145</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Muan al'Halien once lived in an old back-country village in Andor.  He spent his days tending
 the sheep, playing the flute idly as he watched over them.  He lived there to the age of 21,
 then he set out to explore the rest of the world.  His parents, of course, did not want him 
to go, still thinking of him as &quot;their baby.&quot;  There was an argument, and finally he left in 
disgust and headed for Caemlyn.  He knows little, as he discovers in Caemlyn.  Gradually, he 
begins to learn of the world outside of Andor. 
 After an encounter with whitecloaks, watching them harassing a man, he readily dislikes them.
  Every once in a while, an ageless face passes by, that of an Aes Sedai, and he shivers.  He 
still cannot forget the tales from home, though he knows that most are baseless.  He likes to 
work hard, but only at what he likes to do.  He wants to eventually apprentice to a craftsman 
someday.  
After hearing the tales of the Dragon Reborn at his home, he views Rand with much awe and no l
ittle fear.  He is half-way handsome, but not enough that the girls sigh over him.  One of his
 faults is his back-countryness, for he still has only a little knowledge of the world.  Howev
er, once he decides on something, he sticks to it, no matter how long it takes.


</text>
