      <text>This is my application for the Black Tower Guild.  1) Character's Full
Name: Talisen Fallon 2) Character's Channeler Type: Teachable 3)
Character's Background Story:Talisen grew up the son of a well-to-do
merchant in a small village about 30 miles outside the capital of Murandy.
From a small age, Talisen was expected to take over his father's business
when he grew older, and was forc ed to spend most of his younger years
trying to increase his intelligence, especially in business.  For most of
his life, Talisen harbored secret feelings of hatred against his parents,
for choosing his life for him.  His parents studiously ignored any h hints
that he gave them, and he would invariably end up where he started.  He
constantly seeks ways to try to anger his parents, or find some little
things that he can make his own decisions in.  He constantly strives to
make choices for himself, and to be on his own.  4) Character's List of
Strengths:Talisen's main strengths are his intelligence and his drive to
succeed.  He is exceedingly smart, often finding solutions to problems
that few others could, or more inventive solutions than any other person.
He also has a strong will to succeed.  He always tries to see his tasks
through to the end, and always tries to do them to the best of his
abilities.  Character's List of Flaws:His weaknesses include arrogance, a
lack of physical strength, and he is also plagued by self doubt.  Talisen
has a trace of arrogance in his blood, which sometimes leads to him
attempting things that he cannot do, and then fail ing.  When he does
fail, it makes him look even worse, and thus he trys to be even more
arrogant to make up for his foolishness.  He also is plagued by self
doubt, which no doubt led to his overabundance of self confidence.  He
also isn't the most physi cally capable person.  Since he spent so much of
his younger years sharpening his mental acumen, he didn't train his body,
and his skills worsened over time.  5)Method of Recruitment: Active
Recruitment
</text>
